.SH NAME
shelly-provision-wifi - Interactive WiFi provisioning


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBshelly provision wifi  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Provision WiFi settings interactively for a device.

.PP
By default, this command scans for available networks and prompts you to select one.
You can also provide SSID and password directly via flags.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for wifi

.PP
\fB--no-scan\fP[=false]
	Skip network scan, prompt for SSID

.PP
\fB--password\fP=""
	WiFi password

.PP
\fB--ssid\fP=""
	WiFi network name (skip selection)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
